    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A form of spectroscopy in which photoelectrons excited by a beam of monochromatic x-rays are measured in order to find the characteristic binding energies of electrons at particular levels of the sample, thus identifying elements present there.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
